            <title><![CDATA[Pikmin 4 gets free update adding Photo Mode, but no Switch 2 upgrade]]></title>
            <link>https://www.eurogamer.net/pikmin-4-gets-free-update-adding-photo-mode-but-no-switch-2-upgrade</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/pikmin-4-gets-free-update-adding-photo-mode-but-no-switch-2-upgrade.1331620/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>
      <article data-ads="true" data-article-type="news" data-article-group="news" data-paywalled="false" data-premium="false" data-sponsored="false" data-type="article">


<header data-component="article-header">
  

    


  <p>

  <figure>
      <picture>
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Pikmin-4-%E2%80%93-Update-Overview-%E2%80%93-Nintendo-Switch-0-32-screenshot-(1).png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 1dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Pikmin-4-%E2%80%93-Update-Overview-%E2%80%93-Nintendo-Switch-0-32-screenshot-(1).png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.5&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 1.5dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Pikmin-4-%E2%80%93-Update-Overview-%E2%80%93-Nintendo-Switch-0-32-screenshot-(1).png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.75&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 1.75dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Pikmin-4-%E2%80%93-Update-Overview-%E2%80%93-Nintendo-Switch-0-32-screenshot-(1).png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 2dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Pikmin-4-%E2%80%93-Update-Overview-%E2%80%93-Nintendo-Switch-0-32-screenshot-(1).png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=3&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 3dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Pikmin-4-%E2%80%93-Update-Overview-%E2%80%93-Nintendo-Switch-0-32-screenshot-(1).png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Pikmin-4-%E2%80%93-Update-Overview-%E2%80%93-Nintendo-Switch-0-32-screenshot-(1).png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.5&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1.5dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Pikmin-4-%E2%80%93-Update-Overview-%E2%80%93-Nintendo-Switch-0-32-screenshot-(1).png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.75&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1.75dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Pikmin-4-%E2%80%93-Update-Overview-%E2%80%93-Nintendo-Switch-0-32-screenshot-(1).png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 2dppx)">
        
      </picture>

        <figcaption>
          <span>Image credit: <cite>Nintendo</cite></span>
        </figcaption>
  </figure>
  </p>

    

</header>
  <div data-component="article-content">



            <p>Nintendo has announced a free update to <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/pikmin-4">Pikmin 4</a> coming next month, but it doesn't include a <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/digitalfoundry-2025-nintendo-switch-2-the-digital-foundry-hardware-review">Switch 2</a> upgrade.</p>
<p>The update will add a Photo Mode using the new field camera item, with players able to adjust angles and customise images with various decorations.</p>
<p>Decor <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/pikmin">Pikmin</a> will also be added. Originally seen in mobile game <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/pikmin-bloom">Pikmin Bloom</a>, these Pikmin are hidden around levels to be discovered and transferred to your squad - they can also be transferred to the mobile game.</p>

<figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="Pikmin 4 – Update Overview – Nintendo Switch" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/TBtBDFzu9ZA?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
<span>Pikmin 4 – Update Overview – Nintendo Switch</span>
<template>
<iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/TBtBDFzu9ZA?autoplay=1" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/TBtBDFzu9ZA?autoplay=1" title="Pikmin 4 – Update Overview – Nintendo Switch">
</iframe> </template>
</a>
</p>
<figcaption>Pikmin 4 update overview.<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TBtBDFzu9ZA" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>


<p>Lastly, new Creature Activity levels will be added. In Relaxed mode, enemies won't attack unless you attack first, allowing for a breezier challenge, while in Fierce mode they'll be more aggressive.</p>
<p>Though there's no date, the update will arrive in November along with a new demo to try out.</p>
<p>The news follows a <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/nintendo-posts-cute-and-mysterious-animated-short-film-but-is-it-teasing-pikmin">mysterious animated short shared earlier this month called Close to You</a>, which showed a baby being (somewhat) terrorised by invisible creatures. Fans rightly guessed these were Pikmin, and a revised version including the plant critters was published the following day.</p><p>As such, some form of Pikmin news has been expected. But most fans had anticipated an upgraded version of Pikmin 4 for Switch 2 - something Nintendo has released for many of its games, including the two open-world Zelda games, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/kirby-and-the-forgotten-land">Kirby and the Forgotten Land</a>, and Super Mario Party Jamboree. Super Mario Bros. Wonder is also getting an expanded version next year.</p>
<p>But not so Pikmin 4. While the game is playable on the Switch 2, there's no specific upgrade.</p>
<p>Still, it remains a brilliant game on the system. "The Pikmin series blossoms anew, in a bouquet of fresh gameplay and the best bits from its roots," reads our <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/pikmin-4-review-nintendos-oft-overlooked-garden-strategy-reaches-near-perfect-evolution">five star review of Pikmin 4</a>.</p>

        </div>

  
      </article>



  



  

